            "body": "What do you want to have happen differently when clicking a normal/wrapped/virtual part of the statuscolumn? A user supposedly clicks on text/signs in the statuscolumn. What is clicked can be determined with `screenstring(getmouspos()...)` in the click handler callback.\n\nDo you have an example use case that is not served by such a line number + clicked text mapping?\n\nI still don't really think the cost of maintaining a possibly `win_height * <statuscol_width>` store of click handlers is reasonable/worth the trouble.\n",
