        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> [#40265](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/40265) should help, and also paves a way to support per-row click handlers through indexing by lnum + virtnum. One issue is that the same lnum/virtnum index can occur twice if a line has both above/below virtual lines.\n\nThanks! Yeah, judging by description this would make it possible to differentiate between normal/virtual/wrapped lines, but not with [partially hidden statuscolumn lines](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/40210#issuecomment-4698264155). Still an improvement, though 👍",
            "created_at": "2026-06-15T11:41:45Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/40210#issuecomment-4707546838",
